Package ohos.distributedschedule.scenario

Class ScenarioSubscriber

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.distributedschedule.scenario.ScenarioSubscriber

  • public abstract class ScenarioSubscriber
extends Object
    Provides methods for setting distributed scenario subscription information and callbacks invoked when your application is notified upon a scenario status change.

    ScenarioSubscriber is an abstract class. If you want your application to receive notifications upon status changes of specific distributed scenarios, you must first inherit this class and implement the onScenarioNotify(ohos.distributedschedule.scenario.ScenarioResult) method. Then, you can call setSubscribeInfo(ohos.distributedschedule.scenario.SubscribeInfo) to set subscription information and use methods provided in DistributedScenarioManager with your ScenarioSubscriber object passed to subscribe to or unsubscribe from certain distributed scenarios. The received status change result will be stored in ScenarioResult objects.

    Since:
    3
    See Also:
    DistributedScenarioManager.subscribe(ScenarioSubscriber), DistributedScenarioManager.unsubscribe(ScenarioSubscriber)
